    "ReLU is a common option for DL models since it is computationally effective and helps solve the vanishing gradient issue [16].",
    "Deep networks with ReLUs can be optimized more quickly than deep networks with sigmoid or tanh units because gradients can flow when the input to the ReLU function is positive.",
